verbose_text: Wilson et al. showed that Mamu-1 and -3 alleles restrict HIV-1, HIV-2, EIAV, and feline immunodeficiency virus (FIV), but not N-MLV, B-MLV, or SIVmac239, while Mamu-4 and -5 alleles restrict HIV-1, EIAV, and FIV but not HIV-2, N-MLV, B-MLV, or SIVmac239 using a TRIM5alpha transduced cat cell line (CRFK).
evidence: Mamu-4 and -5 alleles restrict HIV-1, EIAV, and FIV but not HIV-2, N-MLV, B-MLV, or SIVmac239 using a TRIM5alpha
